modules.description: Handles incoming HTTP/1.1 connections asynchronously, routing requests to provided handlers. Works with socket addresses and async sockets, processing HTTP requests and errors. Useful for building high-performance, concurrent HTTP servers that handle each connection independently.

Performs HTTP/1.1 client requests over an existing async socket connection. It sends a request, handles errors and responses through provided callbacks, and returns a writeable body for streaming request content. This module is used to implement custom HTTP clients that need precise control over request/response handling and connection reuse.

This module implements asynchronous HTTP/1.1 client and server functionality. The Server module accepts connections, routes requests to handlers, and processes errors using async sockets and socket addresses, enabling high-performance, concurrent HTTP servers. The Client module sends requests over async sockets, streams response content, and handles errors, supporting custom HTTP clients requiring fine-grained control over communication.
